00:00:16.264 --> 00:00:18.793
- So, I was in school
for film and photography,

00:00:18.793 --> 00:00:22.247
looking for animatronics,
special effects work.

00:00:22.247 --> 00:00:23.810
I come down to see a show,

00:00:23.810 --> 00:00:26.055
it was the coolest place I'd ever seen.

00:00:26.055 --> 00:00:28.223
So, I talked to Bob about interning

00:00:28.223 --> 00:00:30.390
and that's how I got here.

00:00:42.007 --> 00:00:44.989
Bob Baker was the world's
greatest puppeteer.

00:00:44.989 --> 00:00:46.053
When he was eight years old,

00:00:46.053 --> 00:00:47.011
he saw this puppet show.

00:00:47.011 --> 00:00:49.415
He spent his whole life kind of creating

00:00:49.415 --> 00:00:52.355
this place and so much more.

00:00:52.355 --> 00:00:54.527
We're more than just 2000 plus puppets,

00:00:54.527 --> 00:00:56.610
we're really representing

00:00:57.661 --> 00:00:58.494
a lifetime,

00:00:58.494 --> 00:01:01.098
and not just Bob's lifetime,

00:01:01.098 --> 00:01:02.711
the lifetime of everyone that's gonna come

00:01:02.711 --> 00:01:06.961
in and out of this building's
experience down here.

00:01:09.336 --> 00:01:10.869
Essentially, the long and the short,

00:01:10.869 --> 00:01:13.132
this is where imagination dwells,

00:01:13.132 --> 00:01:15.294
that's what Bob says.

00:01:15.294 --> 00:01:17.954
So, it's kind of a musical variety,

00:01:17.954 --> 00:01:19.345
spectaculars of

00:01:19.345 --> 00:01:21.787
dancing cats, singing dogs,

00:01:21.787 --> 00:01:23.120
Russian waltzes.

00:01:24.386 --> 00:01:25.677
All sorts of things that kind of

00:01:25.677 --> 00:01:26.875
come to life and kind of

00:01:26.875 --> 00:01:29.026
bring your imagination to life.

00:01:29.026 --> 00:01:31.359
That's for kids of all ages.

00:01:33.300 --> 00:01:35.062
The community here,

00:01:35.062 --> 00:01:37.092
at the theater,

00:01:37.092 --> 00:01:37.938
is

00:01:38.421 --> 00:01:40.037
so big.

00:01:40.508 --> 00:01:43.373
And it represents from our
immediate neighborhood-

00:01:43.373 --> 00:01:44.971
like, Daisy lives across the street,

00:01:44.971 --> 00:01:46.514
now kind of helps us out in spotlight.

00:01:46.514 --> 00:01:47.966
When Bob used to get her ice cream

00:01:47.966 --> 00:01:49.490
when she was like a five year old kid.

00:01:49.490 --> 00:01:50.796
There's like school kids,

00:01:50.796 --> 00:01:52.765
there's generations of puppeteers

00:01:52.765 --> 00:01:54.865
that kind of used to work down here,

00:01:54.865 --> 00:01:56.843
it's free of cynicism or

00:01:56.843 --> 00:01:58.437
messaging or whatever it is,

00:01:58.437 --> 00:02:02.187
it's just "watch your
beautiful puppet dance"

